  {
    "uid": "arxiv:2607.12056v1",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "management",
    "role": "agent",
    "bullets": [
      "Controlled experiment on an e-commerce prototype in two versions, a human-oriented baseline and an agent-ready design with identical catalog, pricing and stock, across five tasks and 300 runs.",
      "Three browser agents, GPT-4.1, Gemini 2.5 Flash and Grok-4 Fast, autonomously searched, compared and purchased products; outcomes scored PASS, PARTIAL or FAIL with no human-coding check.",
      "The agent-ready site reached 89.3 percent strict success versus 49.3 percent for the baseline, cut partial outcomes from 43 to 3, and lowered average steps from 9.31 to 6.49."
    ],
